article.description: Stone Gettings scored 21 points, Robert Hatter added 20 and Cornell finished its season with a 92-78 win over Brown on Saturday night.
article.headline: Cornell finishes season with victory over Brown
article.linkText: Cornell finishes season with victory over Brown
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Stone Gettings scored 21 points, Robert Hatter added 20 and Cornell finished its season with a 92-78 win over Brown on Saturday night. Matt Morgan made three 3-pointers and scored 16 points and Wil Bathurst posted his first career double-double with 12 points and 11 rebounds for the Big Red (8-21, 4-10 Ivy). Steven Spieth sank four 3-pointers and all 11 of his free throws in scoring 31 points while collecting eight rebounds for the Bears (13-17, 4-10). Spieth finished with 1,367 career points, moving up two places to fifth on the school's all-time list. JR Hobbie made five 3-pointers for his 15 points and Obi Okolie added 13 points. Morgan hit a jumper with 15:45 left in the game for a 60-50 lead and the Big Red would go on to lead by as many as 17. Cornell scored the game's first 13 points and never trailed. Cornell shot 59 percent and made 10 of 22 3-point attempts and 22 of 29 free throws.
